.TH "iter_file_splice_write" 9 "iter_file_splice_write" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iter_file_splice_write \- splice data from a pipe to a file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" iter_file_splice_write
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct file *out "  ","
.BI "loff_t *ppos "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "unsigned int flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
pipe info
.IP "out" 12
file to write to
.IP "ppos" 12
position in \fIout\fP
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes to splice
.IP "flags" 12
splice modifier flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Will either move or copy pages (determined by \fIflags\fP options) from
the given pipe inode to the given file.
This one is ->write_iter-based.
